** Junior Broadcast Technologist   
  
**

As part of ARN, the recognised leader in audio in Australia, you have an
opportunity to share your voice on the future of audio. Audio is booming and
we are defining it. We are entertainers. ** We create moments that ** _ move _
** people, and that people ** _ move to _ ** . ** We are investing in audio’s
smartest advertising, experts, and innovations. This gives us unparalleled
understanding of our audience and the content that moves them and helps us
form ** quality connections ** with our customers. It’s our commitment to
creating moments that move people that makes us memorable.  
  
  
  

** We are currently seeking a Junior Broadcast Technologist to join our team in Brisbane! ** This is an exciting role that will be looking after some of Australia’s largest radio shows!   
  
  

The Junior Broadcast Technologist role is an ideal starting point for recent
graduates or individuals embarking on their careers in radio. This entry-level
position offers an exciting opportunity to dive into the world IT and
broadcasting technology.  
  
  

As a ** Junior Broadcast Technologist, ** you will have the chance to work
closely with experienced professionals, gaining hands-on experience in
operating and maintaining studio equipment, troubleshooting technical issues,
and contributing to the seamless execution of live broadcasts. This role
provides a solid foundation for those looking to develop their skills in
broadcasting, signal transmission, and information technology. With ample room
for growth and learning, a Junior Broadcast Technologist can build a strong
foundation for a rewarding and fulfilling career in the ever-evolving realm of
broadcasting.  
  
  

** About the role: **   
  
  

** Broadcasting and Technical Studio Equipment **

  

  * Ensure the effective functioning of broadcasting and streaming equipment, both within studios as a priority and production environments, by responding to and resolving any technical malfunctions or operator issues. 
  * Ensure the preventative maintenance schedule for broadcasting and technical equipment is adhered to, in accordance with quality standards, policy and priorities. 
  * Ensure any additions or changes to infrastructure are documented clearly and accurately. 

** Radio Transmitter Sites **

  

  * Always ensure the effective operation of ARN’s radio transmitter sites and transmission signals by monitoring signals and fail-safe systems. 
  * Ensure the preventative maintenance schedule is adhered to by inspecting the technical equipment and transmitter building sites, in accordance with quality standards, policy and priorities. 

** IT Facilities and Office Equipment **

  

  * Provide hardware and software support for all computer systems. 
  * Assist IT staff to ensure hardware and software support for computers to resolve user issues. 

** About you: **

  

  * Broadcast transmission equipment an advantage. 
  * Audio and visual knowledge. 
  * Excellent time and project management skills. 
  * Sound organizational skills. 
  * Exceptional communication skills both written and verbal. 
  * Technical related knowledge and experience in commercial broadcasting. 
  * Technical related knowledge and experience in information technology. 

** Our Culture:   
  
** We have four behaviours that make up our "Culture in Action" which describe how we act every day to create a great place to work: 

  

  * ** Aim High ** ** ​ ** \- Set big goals and achieve together. 
  * ** Own It ** ​ – Take ownership and be solutions focused. 
  * ** Be Your Best Self ** ​ - Create the environment we need to thrive. 
  * ** Make a Difference ** ​ – Seek out ways to have a positive impact. 

